snippet: The Supreme Court of the Philippines on Tuesday suspended a new Internet law that critics had said could lead to imprisonment for sharing posts on social media.
abstract: Philippines Supreme Court suspends a new Internet law that critics had said could lead to imprisonment for sharing posts on social media.
